benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/resume - Resume a bundle

covered: PUT Method - Valid Request scenarios covered by TC01/TC02/TC03/TC04/TC18 (successful resume with required headers, query params, pluginProperty, and partial input)
PUT Method - Non-Existing Resource covered by TC05 (404 when bundle not found)
PUT Method - State-based errors covered by TC08/TC09 (cannot resume from active or cancelled state)
PUT Method - Input validation and error handling covered by TC06/TC07/TC10/TC19/TC20 (invalid bundleId, missing header, unauthorized, invalid pluginProperty format, past requestedDate)
PUT Method - Security tests covered by TC16/TC17/TC26 (SQL injection in pluginProperty, XSS in comment header, header variations)
PUT Method - Parameter and payload edge cases covered by TC11/TC12/TC13/TC19 (extra parameters, max header lengths, many pluginProperty values, invalid pluginProperty format)
PUT Method - System/Integration/Recovery covered by TC14/TC15/TC25 (dependency service unavailable, retry on transient failure, degraded plugin service)
PUT Method - Performance/Load covered by TC22 (performance under load)
Backward compatibility covered by TC24 (legacy client headers)
Concurrency handling covered by TC21 (concurrent requests)
gaps: Rate limiting / throttling tests (e.g., 429) are not covered
Caching behavior checks (ETag/Cache-Control headers) are not covered
Pagination is not applicable to PUT but no explicit GET pagination tests are provided in this context
Explicit idempotency testing for repeated resumes beyond TC21 could be strengthened
Explicit timeout/timeout propagation tests for degraded services (e.g., 504 on plugin service latency) could be expanded
recommendations: Add a rate-limiting test scenario (429) for rapid consecutive PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/resume calls
Add tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) on responses
Enhance concurrency testing with higher contention and randomized delays to better simulate real-world load
Introduce explicit idempotency tests for repeated resume requests
Add targeted timeout/timeout propagation tests for degraded services with explicit 504 responses
Maintain a regression suite focused on edge cases previously fixed (TC23) to guard against regressions
